<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>250861</id>
	<title>Update Manager automatic updates report false positives</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Build: ZSE6.1-20080907</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Automatic updates report false positives when show the latest version of a feature only checkbox is checked at Help -&gt; Software Updates -&gt; Find and Install -&gt; Search for updates of the currently installed features.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">That is terribly annoying when I come in first thing in the morning, Eclipse always seems to tell me I have updates to look at but when I do, the update list is blank.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Suggested fix:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Preference - "Install/Update -&gt; Automatic Updates" needs checkbox - "Latest version of a feature only" and supporting functionality.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
